	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126408><span id=Sage>Bikamar</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>302 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I double quite often with both hands on my warrior, whom I play mainly (seeing as he is my main).&nbsp;&nbsp;You will double less at lower levels with both hands because your skill is lower.<br><br>Consider this: a check for double attack is made every time you swing with your primary hand.  However, for your secondary hand, first your dual wield check must be passed then the double attack check made - so fewer doubles on the off-hand.<br><br>I wrote a log parser for myself, and that confirms the double attack on off-hand as well. (using 1hs/1hb combo)<br><br>Actually I would have said there were far more 2handers that outdamage 2x 1handers post 50 but *shrugs* that's just me.<br><br>heh ploughing enrage is never a fun thing (well, maybe sometimes =p).  Simply put though if you are in position to plough and you're using a 2 hander, either a) everyone else has really good agro management, b) you're pushing the mob to interrupt or c) you're in the wrong place to be fighting the mob.<br><br>One thing you didn't talk about in your post regarding agro was procs.  Yes, they are important for holding agro. (/wave Enraging Blow)<br>Silly to rely on them? I don't think so, particularly at the higher ends of the game.  And 2 weapons procing &gt; 1 weapon procing.</p>&nbsp;<br>"...come back here ya coward! I'll bite yer kneecaps off..."<br><br>It's not the class that makes the player - it's the player that makes the class</td></td></tr>
