	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Scholar>Yosa</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>194 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.83]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I agree that proc do help with holding agro.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>For a very long time, I used a RBSoN 12/26 with a 176 dd proc.  Which really added to my dps.  <br>Personally I feel it is unwise to rely on them for the following reasons<br>1. proc is a random event, and you can not count on it happing.<br>2. the higher the mob's lvl is compaired to your lvl the less your weapon will proc.  <br><br>If without the proc you will not hold agro, I believe it could prove disisterous for your group or raid.  But if the proc just adds to your ability to hold agro then I would not hesatate to be MA. <br><br>I have used the following weapons with procs<br><br>Yak, I still like this weapon, and at one time it was used well into the 40's.  <br><br>RBSoN I loved this, too bad the one that still drops in the game (if it does) doesent have the proc.<br><br>VAoVB I always felt this weapon was over raited, maybe because it couldn't compete with the RBSoN.  <br><br>Frosty Probably the most popular upper end procing weapons that can be bought.  I personally believe it is good enough to use in your primary hand as well.  However I replaced my with a LSoF. (off hand)  I played around with both for a couple of weeks.  For me I get agro faster and hold it better with the LSoF.<br><br>If I used a weapon with a proc I will try and insure that i get boon.  <br><br>deciding between a weapon with a lower dps and a proc and a weapon with a higher dps is never stright forward.  <br><br>using a Parser and seeing two consitive hits with your off hand weapon on it, or scrolling back and seeing the two hits with your off hand weapons is not prof of a dubble attack with our off hand.  Unless the log has some kind of time stamp or other indication to show both hits happend at the exact same time.  <br>I have seen the off hand weapons score two hits (with some time between them) with no hit scored by the primary weapon.  <br><br>As for 2hw vs 2 1hw for holding agro at lower and mid lvl compaired to high lvls consider the following.<br>Your off hand scored more hits (as a percent of your primary hand) the higher your lvl.  At high lvl (really about 40+ or so) your off hand weapons accounts for a larger percent of your total damage than at lvl 20.  <br>So maybe at lvl 20 the 2hw just has to out damage the primary and 25% of the off hand.  But at lvl 55 it has to out damage the primary and 65% percent of the off hand.  (percents are guess based on observations, not hard numbers)<br><br>After lvl 55+ it is a very rare thing to see a 2hw take and hold agro vs 2 1hw.  I have seen it happen such as with dobble crits.  <br><br>I still use 2hw with my high lvl war, mostly to allow a melee with less ability to hold agro  to hold it when doing so is adventagous to the group or raid.  To see thoes 400 and 500 plus crips.  To keep all my weapon skills lvl maxed.  <br><br>Curently my lower lvl war will use his 2hw to hold agro and to see the reaction of those who believe that two hand weapons are too slow to hold agro effectivly.  I like being different than 99 percent of the warrior.  And I get a big kick out of holding agro with a 50 pp weapon vs weapons that cost 1000s of plat :)<br>Oh btw my warriors are on different servers.  For me most of the fun of eq is improving my toon as they lvl up.  Never was much of a fan of twinking.  <br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
